\title{atomic site}
\taxon{definition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}
\cite{maclane-moerdijk-1994}{Mac Lane & Moerdijk}{p. 115}

\p{Let #{C} be a category so that any [cospan](rs-007H) has a [cocone](rs-001X)
(i.e., #{C} satisfies the \em{right Ore condition}). Then the \em{atomic
topology} on #{C} is the [Grothendieck topology](rs-0079) such that all nonempty
[sieves](rs-0061) are covering.}

